1
00:00:25,955 --> 00:00:29,539
- Hello?
- <i>Hi, honey. I'm at the hospital.</i>

2
00:00:29,623 --> 00:00:31,871
Sorry for not answering your call earlier.

3
00:00:31,955 --> 00:00:34,511
It's fine. I only wanted to tell you...

4
00:00:34,579 --> 00:00:38,123
...that Dr. Rahma is sick,
so she can't attend to patients.

5
00:00:38,207 --> 00:00:42,039
- <i>But they have another doctor.
</i>- What should we do then?

6
00:00:42,123 --> 00:00:44,663
People recommended Dr. Rahma to us.

7
00:00:44,747 --> 00:00:47,871
<i>We're already 10 days late.
We can't postpone our appointment any longer.</i>

8
00:00:47,955 --> 00:00:50,931
Okay, then. As long as you feel comfortable.

9
00:00:51,015 --> 00:00:53,499
- The doctor's young and good.
- A woman or a man?

10
00:00:53,579 --> 00:00:56,163
A man, single, handsome.

11
00:00:56,247 --> 00:00:59,135
That's not what I mean, honey.

12
00:00:59,207 --> 00:01:03,495
I have no problem
if the doctor's a man or a woman as long as...

13
00:01:03,579 --> 00:01:06,999
<i>I'm kidding. It's a woman.
I'm more comfortable with a woman anyway.</i>

14
00:01:07,079 --> 00:01:11,078
I'll call you back later, okay?
Okay. Bye, love you.

15
00:01:12,707 --> 00:01:15,707
- Nurse? Is the ob-gyn here yet?
- Yes, Ma'am?

16
00:01:15,791 --> 00:01:17,623
Ob_gyn?

17
00:01:17,707 --> 00:01:19,206
That's Dr. Cathalina.

18
00:01:25,207 --> 00:01:26,415
Hannah?

19
00:01:27,371 --> 00:01:29,999
Oh, dear! You're Hannah, right?

20
00:01:30,079 --> 00:01:32,747
- I am.
- Oh dear. It's really you.

21
00:01:32,831 --> 00:01:33,915
Han...

22
00:01:35,123 --> 00:01:37,371
Don't you remember who I am?

23
00:01:38,539 --> 00:01:40,955
I'm your high school friend, Han.

24
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:42,123
Cathy.

25
00:01:43,455 --> 00:01:48,831
Cathy? Oh, dear! I didn't recognize you.

26
00:01:48,915 --> 00:01:51,579
- You look so different.
- Do I?

27
00:01:51,663 --> 00:01:53,915
Your hair was short back then.

28
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,499
You're so pretty now, and you're an ob-gyn.

29
00:01:57,579 --> 00:02:00,707
- Let's do your check-up then.
- You're going to do my check-up? Seriously?

30
00:02:00,791 --> 00:02:03,623
What do you mean? You have doubts about me?

31
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:06,955
- Or do you want to cancel your appointment?
- Maybe I should.

32
00:02:07,039 --> 00:02:09,999
Don't. I'm new here.

33
00:02:10,079 --> 00:02:13,955
I'm kidding. I'm happy
that you're the one doing my check-up.

34
00:02:15,047 --> 00:02:18,291
Hang on. Should I call you "Madame Doctor" here?

35
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:24,111
What are you talking about? Relax.
Call me Cathy or whatever, just like we used to.

36
00:02:24,207 --> 00:02:26,503
I should call you "Meow" then.

37
00:02:26,579 --> 00:02:31,331
About your problem,
the sickness and the dizziness...

38
00:02:31,415 --> 00:02:37,331
That's due to your high blood pressure. 143/165.
I'm going to give you pills for that, okay?

39
00:02:37,415 --> 00:02:42,707
But if you're still dizzy after that,
I'll refer you to an internist.

40
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:45,579
Okey dokey, Madame Doctor. Whatever you say.

41
00:02:45,663 --> 00:02:47,662
By the way, are you married yet?

42
00:02:48,955 --> 00:02:53,123
Please, we can only discuss medical issues
in this room, Mrs. Hannah.

43
00:02:53,207 --> 00:02:55,663
Oops, sorry.

44
00:02:55,747 --> 00:02:57,247
Let's start.

45
00:02:58,623 --> 00:03:00,083
How's my baby?

46
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:03,539
- A boy?
- He is.

47
00:03:03,623 --> 00:03:05,291
You must be so happy.

48
00:03:05,371 --> 00:03:08,999
The fetus' weight is normal.

49
00:03:09,079 --> 00:03:13,079
See? The placenta is also in the right place.
It's good.

50
00:03:13,163 --> 00:03:16,999
And the fetus' head is near the birth canal.

51
00:03:19,123 --> 00:03:23,414
The growth is slow, but we'll find out the cause.

52
00:03:27,039 --> 00:03:30,871
Han, you don't need to worry. This is common.

53
00:03:30,955 --> 00:03:35,371
It's usually because
the mother doesn't get enough nutrition.

54
00:03:35,455 --> 00:03:37,415
Yes, Madame Doctor.

55
00:03:37,499 --> 00:03:40,791
For me to eat a lot, I have one condition.

56
00:03:40,871 --> 00:03:46,247
Madame Doctor must come and eat with me at my house.

57
00:03:46,331 --> 00:03:50,623
This is the first time
I have a patient giving me a condition.

58
00:03:50,707 --> 00:03:51,998
But you'll do it, won't you?

59
00:03:52,079 --> 00:03:55,539
- Let me think about it first.
- Oh, dear. What a busy doctor.

60
00:03:55,623 --> 00:03:58,622
Hey, your husband did not come with you?

61
00:04:00,163 --> 00:04:03,747
He had a meeting.
But I think he's on his way here.

62
00:04:03,831 --> 00:04:07,162
By the way, I don't know who your husband is.
Who is he?

63
00:04:08,831 --> 00:04:12,791
We can only discuss medical issues in this room.

64
00:04:12,871 --> 00:04:16,610
- Okay. You are using my own words against me?
- Who said that earlier?

65
00:04:33,663 --> 00:04:35,914
Okay. Thank you, Sir.

66
00:04:39,207 --> 00:04:42,287
- Hi!
- Hi!

67
00:04:42,371 --> 00:04:46,955
Welcome! Finally, you're here!

68
00:04:47,039 --> 00:04:48,954
Come in.

69
00:04:52,247 --> 00:04:56,663
Han, you have such a nice house. Great ambiance.

70
00:04:56,747 --> 00:04:59,207
Thank you. Let's go to the back
to meet my husband.

71
00:04:59,291 --> 00:05:02,455
He's cooking us dinner. He won't let me get tired.

72
00:05:03,663 --> 00:05:06,831
Here he is. Honey, here's my doctor.

73
00:05:06,915 --> 00:05:07,914
Oh, yeah.

74
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:18,291
Titi?

75
00:05:18,371 --> 00:05:19,498
Malik?

76
00:05:20,411 --> 00:05:22,326
Surprise!

77
00:05:26,791 --> 00:05:30,415
- Happy? Are you happy now, Mrs. Hannah?
- I am.

78
00:05:31,579 --> 00:05:35,707
No wonder she wouldn't mention
who her husband is. It's you.

79
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:38,623
Hannah didn't tell me either
that you're her doctor friend.

80
00:05:38,707 --> 00:05:41,499
I did it on purpose.
I wanted to see your reactions.

81
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:45,622
You still love to play around, don't you?

82
00:05:49,955 --> 00:05:52,123
Hang on. You guys talk.

83
00:05:52,207 --> 00:05:53,623
Hannah? Where are you going?

84
00:05:53,707 --> 00:05:55,706
Just a minute. Just chat a bit.

85
00:06:39,371 --> 00:06:40,831
Do you know?

86
00:06:40,915 --> 00:06:46,999
If I start to grumble and get angry,
he can't take it. And he would instantly say...

87
00:06:47,079 --> 00:06:51,539
..."Honey, I married you because you're funny.

88
00:06:51,623 --> 00:06:54,079
You're not funny anymore if you're angry."

89
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:57,539
Does he think I'm a comedian?
He married me just because I'm funny?

90
00:06:57,623 --> 00:07:01,623
It's not that, honey. But you make me happy.

91
00:07:02,623 --> 00:07:03,791
Honey...

92
00:07:03,871 --> 00:07:06,579
These kinds of things melt my heart.

93
00:07:06,663 --> 00:07:09,331
But where did you meet again?

94
00:07:09,415 --> 00:07:13,415
We met again in Jogja
because we were studying at the same university.

95
00:07:13,499 --> 00:07:15,791
We were just friends back in high school.

96
00:07:15,871 --> 00:07:20,371
But because Jogja has romantic vibes, so...

97
00:07:20,455 --> 00:07:21,539
...the rest is history.

98
00:07:21,623 --> 00:07:26,123
But who didn't like him back in high school?
Every girl had a crush on him.

99
00:07:26,207 --> 00:07:29,538
Including you, right? You had a crush on him
back in high school, didn't you?

100
00:07:32,039 --> 00:07:34,122
So cute.

101
00:07:40,915 --> 00:07:42,791
Do you have a husband?

102
00:07:42,871 --> 00:07:44,291
Not yet, honey.

103
00:07:44,371 --> 00:07:50,207
Can't you see? A doctor, pretty, successful.
Guys are afraid of her.

104
00:07:50,291 --> 00:07:52,999
It's not like that. You're exaggerating.

105
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:57,707
I just haven't met the right guy.

106
00:07:57,791 --> 00:07:59,459
Your standard is too high.

107
00:07:59,523 --> 00:08:01,762
What?

108
00:08:08,079 --> 00:08:10,079
Excuse me, I need to get this.

109
00:08:10,163 --> 00:08:11,290
Please.

110
00:08:15,663 --> 00:08:16,707
Hello?

111
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:19,491
Yes?

112
00:08:19,915 --> 00:08:20,999
What?

113
00:08:22,079 --> 00:08:23,414
Mrs. Dewi?

114
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:26,791
Okay. I'll be there in a second.

115
00:08:26,871 --> 00:08:28,623
Wait for me, okay?

116
00:08:31,539 --> 00:08:37,079
Hannah, Malik, I'm sorry.
I need to go to the hospital for an emergency.

117
00:08:37,163 --> 00:08:40,915
It's okay. You got here by taxi, didn't you?
Honey, take her.

118
00:08:40,999 --> 00:08:46,707
- No, it's fine. I can go by taxi.
- No way. It's dark. The hospital's not far anyway.

119
00:08:46,791 --> 00:08:48,955
It's okay. Let me take you. I'll get ready.

120
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:50,387
- Okay.
- But...

121
00:08:50,455 --> 00:08:52,291
It's fine.

122
00:08:52,371 --> 00:08:55,331
Han, you're okay with Malik taking me to the hospital?

123
00:08:55,415 --> 00:08:59,079
It's okay. I trust you.

124
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:02,414
There's no way a woman like you would
want to be with another woman's husband.

125
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:20,755
Malik?

126
00:09:20,831 --> 00:09:22,955
- Hey, Cath.
- You're still here?

127
00:09:23,039 --> 00:09:24,791
I was waiting for you.

128
00:09:25,743 --> 00:09:28,743
The weather is bad.
I will be worried if you took a cab.

129
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:33,371
But I have ordered one.

130
00:09:33,455 --> 00:09:34,746
You can cancel it, right?

131
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:47,414
I still can't believe you're a doctor now
since you were afraid to see blood.

132
00:09:52,499 --> 00:09:55,247
- Good evening, Uncle.
- Good evening.

133
00:09:55,331 --> 00:09:56,747
Good evening, Aunty.

134
00:09:58,499 --> 00:10:01,662
Mom, do you still remember him?

135
00:10:05,087 --> 00:10:06,587
I'm Malik, Aunty, Uncle.

136
00:10:06,671 --> 00:10:09,871
Oh, Malik! Oh dear!

137
00:10:09,955 --> 00:10:11,454
Why are you here together?

138
00:10:12,831 --> 00:10:18,499
I'll tell you later. He better go home now.
His wife is waiting for him back home.

139
00:10:18,579 --> 00:10:21,791
Oh, you're married.

140
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:24,163
- Do you have any children?
- My wife's pregnant.

141
00:10:24,247 --> 00:10:26,291
Here's the doctor.

142
00:10:26,371 --> 00:10:28,791
Thank you for bringing Cathy home.

143
00:10:28,871 --> 00:10:31,499
I'm leaving, Uncle, Aunty.

144
00:10:31,579 --> 00:10:33,663
- Okay. Thanks.
- Aunty.

145
00:10:33,747 --> 00:10:36,998
I'll drop him to his car.

146
00:10:43,715 --> 00:10:45,915
Hey. Don't be nosy.

147
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,162
What are you talking about?

148
00:11:07,207 --> 00:11:08,247
Na?

149
00:11:10,863 --> 00:11:11,862
Nana?

150
00:11:13,331 --> 00:11:14,831
Na?

151
00:11:14,915 --> 00:11:17,539
Nana? Oh, dear. Hannah!

152
00:11:17,623 --> 00:11:20,415
Hannah?

153
00:11:20,499 --> 00:11:23,539
Nana?

154
00:11:23,623 --> 00:11:24,511
Na?

155
00:11:24,579 --> 00:11:26,122
Oh, dear. Hannah?

156
00:11:34,163 --> 00:11:37,791
- Hannah.
- Morning, Doctor.

157
00:11:37,871 --> 00:11:39,998
How are you doing? Are you okay?

158
00:11:40,079 --> 00:11:43,998
How do I look? I look fine, don't I?
Still looking pretty?

159
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:48,247
I'm fine, Cath.

160
00:11:48,331 --> 00:11:51,247
They checked the baby last night.

161
00:11:51,331 --> 00:11:53,791
Thank God, all is safe.

162
00:11:53,871 --> 00:11:56,707
And what did Doctor Mulia say?

163
00:11:56,791 --> 00:12:00,039
We're going to get a CT scan now.

164
00:12:00,123 --> 00:12:04,079
- Okay.
- I have to be okay...

165
00:12:04,163 --> 00:12:07,623
...so I don't die first and you remarry.

166
00:12:07,707 --> 00:12:10,538
- What? What are you talking about?
- I won't allow it.

167
00:12:12,247 --> 00:12:14,915
Enough. Let's go to the radiology.

168
00:12:15,831 --> 00:12:18,539
- Excuse us.
- Can you accompany us? You can't?

169
00:12:18,623 --> 00:12:20,663
- I can't.
- Stop it.

170
00:12:20,747 --> 00:12:23,123
- But let me know the result.
- Okay.

171
00:12:23,207 --> 00:12:26,123
- Okay, bye.
- I'll call you. Bye, Cath.

172
00:12:26,419 --> 00:12:27,886
Are you okay?

173
00:12:28,287 --> 00:12:30,294
I'm okay.

174
00:12:38,831 --> 00:12:42,955
How did it feel
when you came to know Hannah's husband is Malik?

175
00:12:43,039 --> 00:12:46,707
I bet you wanted to pull her hair.

176
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:49,499
Ra, you're overthinking.

177
00:12:49,579 --> 00:12:52,623
Cathy isn't like that. Am I right?

178
00:12:52,707 --> 00:12:56,371
See? She's silent. It means she agrees with me.

179
00:12:56,455 --> 00:12:58,954
Cath, does your heart still hurt?

180
00:13:00,623 --> 00:13:02,163
What should I say?

181
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:06,787
My heart's not hurting anymore. But...

182
00:13:06,871 --> 00:13:08,579
...when I saw his face...

183
00:13:09,707 --> 00:13:11,663
...I wanted to scratch his face.

184
00:13:11,747 --> 00:13:13,303
See?

185
00:13:14,039 --> 00:13:16,539
I'm with you.

186
00:13:16,623 --> 00:13:20,663
- Do you still love him?
- What are you talking about? I'm only kidding.

187
00:13:20,747 --> 00:13:24,455
- You're exaggerating.
- I don't love him anymore, okay?

188
00:13:24,539 --> 00:13:28,163
Can we change the topic?
I'm sick of talking about this.

189
00:13:28,247 --> 00:13:30,871
I'm not even thinking about it too much.

190
00:13:30,955 --> 00:13:36,355
Okay. You say now you don't want to talk
or think about him.

191
00:13:36,455 --> 00:13:43,247
But you know, deep down,
the names Malik and Hannah are in your mind.

192
00:13:43,331 --> 00:13:47,746
That's the reason you haven't moved on yet.
You still want to be single, don't you?

193
00:13:48,915 --> 00:13:52,871
Me being single right now...

194
00:13:52,955 --> 00:13:55,291
...one thing for sure is
he's not the reason for it.

195
00:13:55,371 --> 00:13:57,371
Because you haven't found a guy like Malik.

196
00:13:59,207 --> 00:14:04,206
Guys, I have moved on. Okay?

197
00:14:14,747 --> 00:14:15,830
How is it, Doc?

198
00:14:17,415 --> 00:14:18,623
I'm sorry.

199
00:14:19,499 --> 00:14:23,498
But I have to tell you this bad news.

200
00:14:24,679 --> 00:14:26,930
The CT scan result shows...

201
00:14:28,123 --> 00:14:29,370
...the presence of cancer.

202
00:14:38,207 --> 00:14:42,499
Doctor, are you certain?
Any possibility of a mistake?

203
00:14:42,579 --> 00:14:44,579
This is not what we hoped for.

204
00:14:44,663 --> 00:14:50,290
The biopsy shows
that Mrs. Hannah has stage 3 brain cancer.

205
00:14:53,123 --> 00:14:54,955
What should we do now, Doc?

206
00:14:55,039 --> 00:14:59,747
Because you're pregnant,
you need to be handled with special treatment.

207
00:14:59,831 --> 00:15:01,871
Chemo is the most suitable treatment.

208
00:15:01,955 --> 00:15:05,078
I'll discuss it first with the ob-gyn.

209
00:15:09,163 --> 00:15:12,831
I've read about it and found out...

210
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:20,039
...that chemo poses a high risk for the fetus.

211
00:15:20,123 --> 00:15:21,791
So, I'm not going to do it.

212
00:15:21,871 --> 00:15:25,998
Honey, if you're not going to do it,
It’s very risky for you.

213
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:29,207
If I do it...

214
00:15:30,291 --> 00:15:32,499
...it's very risky for the baby.

215
00:15:32,579 --> 00:15:35,998
And the most important thing now is my baby.

216
00:15:36,079 --> 00:15:40,039
But if something happens to you,
it'll affect the baby.

217
00:15:41,123 --> 00:15:44,163
I'm going to have the chemo
after my baby is born. End of story.

218
00:15:44,247 --> 00:15:46,831
You have to be serious about it.
It's your life we're talking about.

219
00:15:46,915 --> 00:15:51,831
I don't mind losing my life,
as long as my baby is born safely.

220
00:15:51,915 --> 00:15:53,539
Oh, dear.

221
00:15:53,623 --> 00:15:54,915
Honey, don't be stubborn.

222
00:15:54,999 --> 00:15:58,415
- Just this time, don't be stubborn. Think about yourself.
- Don't you love your baby?

223
00:15:58,499 --> 00:16:00,371
- I do.
- Hannah, Malik.

224
00:16:02,035 --> 00:16:03,279
Stop it.

225
00:16:03,831 --> 00:16:06,162
Don't get too emotional. Calm down.

226
00:16:08,123 --> 00:16:10,955
The situation must be hard for both of you.

227
00:16:11,039 --> 00:16:15,370
Han, as a patient, you have the right
to reject a medical procedure.

228
00:16:16,871 --> 00:16:18,663
But you also need to understand...

229
00:16:18,747 --> 00:16:22,747
...that a doctor's recommendation
is based on a patient's medical record.

230
00:16:22,831 --> 00:16:27,871
That's why a patient and a doctor
need to be in agreement.

231
00:16:27,955 --> 00:16:30,331
Then only can the medical procedure be done.

232
00:16:30,415 --> 00:16:31,662
In your opinion...

233
00:16:32,999 --> 00:16:34,331
...as a good friend...

234
00:16:35,455 --> 00:16:36,791
...not as a doctor...

235
00:16:39,871 --> 00:16:41,207
...what should we do?

236
00:16:43,415 --> 00:16:44,875
As a good friend...

237
00:16:47,623 --> 00:16:49,998
...I want you to get through
the medical procedure, Han.

238
00:16:52,579 --> 00:16:53,870
For your own good.

239
00:17:02,207 --> 00:17:04,714
Honey... Do it, okay?

240
00:17:08,747 --> 00:17:11,098
Just leave.

241
00:17:12,123 --> 00:17:13,331
- Bye.
- Bye.

242
00:17:14,247 --> 00:17:16,747
- Mbok, take care of her. She's unwell.
- Yes, Sir.

243
00:17:17,915 --> 00:17:19,454
- Bye, honey.
- Bye.

244
00:17:25,663 --> 00:17:30,207
My husband never kissed me when he left,
he kicked me instead.

245
00:17:31,291 --> 00:17:33,623
Ma'am, what's wrong?

246
00:17:33,707 --> 00:17:35,003
- What's wrong?
- I'm fine.

247
00:17:35,087 --> 00:17:36,955
I'll call Mr. Malik
to take you to the doctor, okay?

248
00:17:37,039 --> 00:17:39,871
No, he has just left.

249
00:17:39,955 --> 00:17:44,455
You know, it's only because I'm pregnant.

250
00:17:44,539 --> 00:17:47,954
I see. I was like that when I was pregnant.

251
00:17:48,039 --> 00:17:51,455
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Dizzy and sick...

252
00:17:51,539 --> 00:17:53,539
...of seeing my husband not have anything to do.

253
00:17:55,707 --> 00:17:57,831
- Not that angle.
- How should I do it then?

254
00:17:57,915 --> 00:18:02,415
- My face looks big. A bit lower.
- Oh, dear.

255
00:18:02,499 --> 00:18:07,371
It's usually the photographer
that gives the direction, not the model.

256
00:18:07,455 --> 00:18:08,707
Good evening.

257
00:18:08,791 --> 00:18:11,122
- Aunty, Uncle.
- Erol.

258
00:18:13,123 --> 00:18:15,039
How are you?
It's been a while since you came here.

259
00:18:15,123 --> 00:18:16,455
- Good evening.
- Erol.

260
00:18:16,539 --> 00:18:20,623
I just got back from a two-month trip around Europe.
For business.

261
00:18:20,707 --> 00:18:22,291
- Amazing.
- With your dad?

262
00:18:22,371 --> 00:18:25,663
With my dad.
But I handle a lot of Dad's business now.

263
00:18:25,747 --> 00:18:27,747
Cool. That's how it should be.

264
00:18:27,831 --> 00:18:31,207
Youngsters nowadays have to take part,
not be standing behind their parents.

265
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:34,623
- Give my regards to your dad.
- I will.

266
00:18:34,707 --> 00:18:37,207
Let's drink some tea.
I made some great cookies.

267
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:41,079
Thank you, but not for me. I'm only picking Cathy up.
It's okay for me to take her out, isn't it?

268
00:18:41,163 --> 00:18:45,123
Of course. Call your sister.

269
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:47,914
Big sister! Erol's here!

270
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,663
- Oh dear!
- Erol's here!

271
00:18:50,747 --> 00:18:53,415
Don't scream. Go in and get her.

272
00:18:53,499 --> 00:18:57,662
- That's not how you do it.
- Kids nowadays.

273
00:19:00,539 --> 00:19:02,870
I could hear your loud voice all the way inside.

274
00:19:04,123 --> 00:19:06,123
- Hi, Cath.
- Hi.

275
00:19:07,539 --> 00:19:09,791
Mom, Dad, I'm leaving, okay?

276
00:19:09,871 --> 00:19:11,663
Okay.

277
00:19:11,747 --> 00:19:13,663
- So pretty.
- Cathy.

278
00:19:13,747 --> 00:19:15,623
Don't come home too late at night. Okay?

279
00:19:15,707 --> 00:19:18,954
And Erol? Take care of my daughter.
Bring her home in one piece.

280
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,039
For sure.

281
00:19:21,091 --> 00:19:22,039
You're still joking.

282
00:19:22,123 --> 00:19:23,663
- Aunty, Uncle.
- Yeah.

283
00:19:23,747 --> 00:19:24,914
Bye.

284
00:19:28,331 --> 00:19:33,123
The restaurant is great,
but why are there no other customers?

285
00:19:33,207 --> 00:19:36,747
I booked it just for the two of us.

286
00:19:38,855 --> 00:19:41,707
Rol, isn't this a bit too much?

287
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:43,870
No way. It's for you.

288
00:19:45,707 --> 00:19:49,039
I also have ordered the food for you.
Is that okay?

289
00:19:49,123 --> 00:19:51,830
It's okay. I trust your judgment.

290
00:19:54,331 --> 00:19:55,662
When I was in Europe...

291
00:19:56,871 --> 00:20:00,579
...Dad urged me to make a choice immediately.

292
00:20:00,663 --> 00:20:03,791
He said I need to make a commitment
to a partner...

293
00:20:03,871 --> 00:20:06,039
...before he gives his business to me.

294
00:20:07,539 --> 00:20:09,871
Well...

295
00:20:09,955 --> 00:20:15,986
...someone who is married
is usually more capable to make a commitment.

296
00:20:16,079 --> 00:20:19,330
That's why I want to make a commitment to you.

297
00:20:20,371 --> 00:20:24,623
I want us to not only be friends.

298
00:20:24,707 --> 00:20:27,830
So, that's what your dad wants?

299
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:30,538
That's what I want too.

300
00:20:32,623 --> 00:20:36,539
- Why are you laughing?
- Nothing. I just want to laugh. Can't I?

301
00:20:36,623 --> 00:20:37,623
So, what do you think?

302
00:20:39,247 --> 00:20:40,454
So...

303
00:20:58,623 --> 00:20:59,662
No.

304
00:21:00,999 --> 00:21:01,999
No?

305
00:21:03,163 --> 00:21:05,331
Yes, no.

306
00:21:05,415 --> 00:21:08,831
Please tell your dad sorry.

307
00:21:08,915 --> 00:21:11,371
No problem. It's fine.

308
00:21:11,455 --> 00:21:17,123
If I can be honest,
I'm more comfortable if we're friends.

309
00:21:17,207 --> 00:21:20,207
Me, too. As long as you're comfortable, right?

310
00:21:20,291 --> 00:21:21,315
Thank you.

311
00:21:21,379 --> 00:21:22,379
Okay.

312
00:21:23,163 --> 00:21:24,747
Thank you.

313
00:21:26,999 --> 00:21:28,122
Let's eat.

314
00:21:33,707 --> 00:21:34,746
Hello?

315
00:21:37,371 --> 00:21:40,915
Okay. I'm on my way there. Hang on.

316
00:21:42,123 --> 00:21:46,415
Rol, I'm so sorry. But I need to go to the hospital.
There's an emergency.

317
00:21:46,499 --> 00:21:47,622
Okay, but eat first.

318
00:21:49,331 --> 00:21:50,579
They can wait, can't they?

319
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,415
They can't.

320
00:21:53,499 --> 00:21:57,207
Someone's life is in my hands.
I need to leave now.

321
00:21:57,291 --> 00:21:59,622
You don't need to take me, I'll get a taxi.

322
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:15,747
Cathy, sorry for this.

323
00:22:15,831 --> 00:22:18,623
It’s ok. It's my job. How's Hannah?

324
00:22:18,707 --> 00:22:19,954
I don't know.

325
00:22:20,039 --> 00:22:22,706
Doc, how's my wife?

326
00:22:25,579 --> 00:22:28,999
There's no other way.
We need to deliver the baby now.

327
00:22:29,079 --> 00:22:32,499
But with the patient's condition, it'll be risky.

328
00:22:33,955 --> 00:22:35,707
Excuse me, Sir. Your wife's asking for you.

329
00:22:35,791 --> 00:22:36,999
Okay.

330
00:22:37,079 --> 00:22:38,454
- Doc...
- Please.

331
00:22:41,747 --> 00:22:43,954
Doc, I'm sorry, but I...

332
00:22:44,331 --> 00:22:45,663
I know.

333
00:22:45,747 --> 00:22:48,207
You have an emotional attachment to the patient.

334
00:22:48,291 --> 00:22:51,331
But if you mind,
another doctor can take your place.

335
00:22:51,415 --> 00:22:53,039
But the surgery needs to be done soon.

336
00:22:53,123 --> 00:22:56,371
At least one life will be saved.

337
00:22:59,163 --> 00:23:00,207
Okay, Doc.

338
00:23:01,291 --> 00:23:04,955
I'm ready, because there's no other option, isn't it?

339
00:23:06,039 --> 00:23:09,407
I don't care what's going to happen to me anymore.

340
00:23:11,039 --> 00:23:12,458
I need your help.

341
00:23:16,663 --> 00:23:18,538
Save my baby, Cath.

342
00:23:21,495 --> 00:23:22,719
Han...

343
00:23:23,371 --> 00:23:25,915
...everything's going to be okay.

344
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,038
Okay?

345
00:23:29,579 --> 00:23:30,870
I hope...

346
00:23:33,791 --> 00:23:37,207
...I can die in peace.

347
00:23:39,079 --> 00:23:41,662
I know I won't make it.

348
00:23:44,871 --> 00:23:47,078
I'm sure you actually know it too.

349
00:23:49,291 --> 00:23:50,415
Honey...

350
00:23:51,611 --> 00:23:53,999
You'll be healthy again.

351
00:23:54,079 --> 00:23:55,206
Got it?

352
00:23:58,087 --> 00:24:00,959
Cathy, Malik...

353
00:24:01,983 --> 00:24:05,806
...I know both of you
still have feelings for each other.

354
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:18,291
Han...

355
00:24:18,371 --> 00:24:19,299
Han...

356
00:24:19,371 --> 00:24:23,246
- Don't think bad thoughts about me.
- I'm not having bad thoughts.

357
00:24:26,079 --> 00:24:27,954
For me, it's good.

358
00:24:29,627 --> 00:24:33,626
I will be in peace and happy...

359
00:24:36,031 --> 00:24:37,698
...if you get married.

360
00:24:45,247 --> 00:24:48,635
Han, I'm sorry, but it's not funny.

361
00:24:50,247 --> 00:24:53,039
Ti, sorry, Hannah's mind is down, so...

362
00:24:54,163 --> 00:24:56,831
That's why she's talking nonsense.

363
00:24:56,915 --> 00:24:58,891
I'm serious.

364
00:24:58,955 --> 00:25:00,871
- Honey, what are you talking about?
- I'm serious.

365
00:25:03,579 --> 00:25:07,406
Cath, I want my baby safe...

366
00:25:08,871 --> 00:25:11,790
...and taken care of by someone right.

367
00:25:13,623 --> 00:25:15,790
Malik is also a good husband.

368
00:25:18,823 --> 00:25:23,946
I don't want him to marry the wrong woman.

369
00:25:27,831 --> 00:25:28,831
Han...

370
00:25:30,791 --> 00:25:34,790
You know I care so much about you.

371
00:25:37,079 --> 00:25:38,602
But I'm sorry...

372
00:25:40,207 --> 00:25:42,787
...I can't do what you are asking from me.

373
00:25:43,663 --> 00:25:45,111
I can't.

374
00:25:45,899 --> 00:25:49,354
You better rest now to calm your mind.

375
00:25:52,999 --> 00:25:54,414
Ti, sorry...

376
00:26:26,499 --> 00:26:28,371
Honey, what's wrong with you?

377
00:26:28,455 --> 00:26:31,123
Stop it. Don't talk nonsense.

378
00:26:31,207 --> 00:26:33,706
I never asked anything from you.

379
00:26:36,247 --> 00:26:37,330
Only this.

380
00:26:52,539 --> 00:26:54,579
I want my baby safe...

381
00:26:55,955 --> 00:26:58,790
...and taken care of by someone right.

382
00:27:01,371 --> 00:27:03,414
Malik is also a good husband.

383
00:27:04,747 --> 00:27:09,998
I don't want him to marry the wrong woman.

384
00:28:19,207 --> 00:28:22,079
You can ask anything you want.

385
00:28:22,163 --> 00:28:24,331
But not that.

386
00:28:24,415 --> 00:28:26,039
I don't want anything else.

387
00:28:27,247 --> 00:28:28,538
Just that.

388
00:28:35,207 --> 00:28:36,330
Ti.

389
00:28:46,039 --> 00:28:47,290
I agree to do it.

390
00:28:52,707 --> 00:28:53,915
Seriously, Cath?

391
00:28:55,539 --> 00:28:56,871
Ti, let's talk.

392
00:28:56,955 --> 00:28:59,206
Hey. What for?

393
00:29:00,247 --> 00:29:01,830
She's ready to do it.

394
00:29:04,539 --> 00:29:07,914
Honey, listen to me.
You're going to be healthy again.

395
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,955
I have a feeling.

396
00:29:11,123 --> 00:29:13,498
And I'm sure it's going to come true.

397
00:29:20,151 --> 00:29:21,150
Cath...

398
00:29:26,915 --> 00:29:28,291
Say what I'm about to say.

399
00:29:30,079 --> 00:29:31,578
In the name of Allah...

400
00:29:33,975 --> 00:29:36,367
Honey, it's impossible. Okay?

401
00:29:37,291 --> 00:29:39,623
Titi has a different belief from us.

402
00:29:39,707 --> 00:29:40,914
Stop it.

403
00:29:44,163 --> 00:29:45,746
I'm also a Muslim, Malik.

404
00:29:51,123 --> 00:29:52,746
I should be able to do it.

405
00:30:04,247 --> 00:30:06,914
You had to break up
because of your different beliefs.

406
00:30:09,247 --> 00:30:14,162
But there's no more reason
for you to not be together.

407
00:30:16,407 --> 00:30:17,407
Cath...

408
00:30:18,707 --> 00:30:20,078
Say what I'm about to say, okay?

409
00:30:24,791 --> 00:30:25,954
In the name of Allah...

410
00:30:29,871 --> 00:30:30,914
Cath...

411
00:30:32,207 --> 00:30:33,578
In the name of Allah...

412
00:30:37,955 --> 00:30:40,830
Come on, Cath. You promised me.

413
00:30:45,123 --> 00:30:46,290
"In the name of Allah..."

414
00:30:48,207 --> 00:30:49,623
In the name of Allah...

415
00:30:51,831 --> 00:30:54,123
"I will...

416
00:30:55,027 --> 00:30:57,110
...marry your husband."

417
00:31:02,955 --> 00:31:05,039
Go on. Say it.

418
00:31:06,871 --> 00:31:08,038
Cath.

419
00:31:14,539 --> 00:31:16,415
If God permits it...

420
00:31:18,291 --> 00:31:21,290
...I will marry...

421
00:31:30,663 --> 00:31:31,914
...your husband.

422
00:31:43,079 --> 00:31:45,123
Thank you.

423
00:31:45,207 --> 00:31:47,454
You could always calm me down.

424
00:31:51,371 --> 00:31:55,206
I want to see you get married before my surgery.

425
00:32:02,207 --> 00:32:04,623
Han, it's impossible.

426
00:32:04,707 --> 00:32:09,747
I'm willing and I will do it
if what you're worried about really happens.

427
00:32:09,831 --> 00:32:11,291
But if not...

428
00:32:11,371 --> 00:32:13,371
...I can't.

429
00:32:13,455 --> 00:32:17,663
So how will I know
you're going to keep your promise...

430
00:32:17,747 --> 00:32:20,706
...if I'm not here anymore?

431
00:32:24,415 --> 00:32:26,955
Enough. It's not right.

432
00:32:27,039 --> 00:32:29,371
Take back your request. Okay?

433
00:32:29,455 --> 00:32:31,370
But Cathy has sworn.

434
00:32:32,855 --> 00:32:37,078
This is the only thing that will keep me calm
during the surgery.

435
00:32:40,539 --> 00:32:43,414
I'd like to be your marriage witness.

436
00:32:48,955 --> 00:32:52,835
I think Hannah knows
that you only want to make her happy.

437
00:32:55,039 --> 00:32:57,747
But don't you worry, okay?
Don't think about it.

438
00:32:57,831 --> 00:33:00,623
Let me take care of this.
I'll talk to Hannah.

439
00:33:01,467 --> 00:33:04,139
I'll try to make her understand. Okay?

440
00:33:06,123 --> 00:33:07,414
Let's do it tomorrow.

441
00:33:09,551 --> 00:33:10,550
What?

442
00:33:16,707 --> 00:33:17,994
Let's get married tomorrow.

443
00:33:21,751 --> 00:33:23,750
What are you doing this for, huh?

444
00:33:25,955 --> 00:33:30,123
I don't want you to sacrifice your future
just because you pity me and Hannah.

445
00:33:30,999 --> 00:33:31,998
We...

446
00:33:33,371 --> 00:33:34,578
...are doing this...

447
00:33:36,371 --> 00:33:37,455
...for Hannah.

448
00:33:38,791 --> 00:33:39,914
That's the only reason?

449
00:33:41,455 --> 00:33:43,162
What other reasons do you want?

450
00:33:47,579 --> 00:33:48,579
Because...

451
00:33:49,663 --> 00:33:52,163
Because I still love you?

452
00:33:52,247 --> 00:33:54,791
Because when you left me...

453
00:33:54,871 --> 00:33:57,747
...I felt lost and I still had hope
to get back with you again?

454
00:33:58,679 --> 00:34:00,006
Is that what you mean?

455
00:34:05,295 --> 00:34:06,378
I...

456
00:34:09,619 --> 00:34:12,119
...have no feelings for you anymore.

457
00:34:14,175 --> 00:34:16,227
And I'm going to marry you...

458
00:34:17,139 --> 00:34:18,391
...just for Hannah...

459
00:34:19,579 --> 00:34:21,539
...and the baby in her womb.

460
00:34:22,663 --> 00:34:24,455
One more thing.

461
00:34:24,539 --> 00:34:27,415
I didn't become a Muslim because of you.

462
00:34:27,499 --> 00:34:30,954
I became a Muslim because I wanted to learn Islam.

463
00:34:32,371 --> 00:34:35,122
And I learned about it when I studied in England.

464
00:34:36,019 --> 00:34:37,895
We were broken up at that time.

465
00:34:39,079 --> 00:34:41,539
So whatever my decision is...

466
00:34:41,623 --> 00:34:44,663
...I am doing it all from my heart.

467
00:34:46,247 --> 00:34:47,954
It doesn't have anything to do with you.

468
00:34:49,623 --> 00:34:51,207
And I'm certain...

469
00:34:51,291 --> 00:34:52,371
...Hannah...

470
00:34:53,791 --> 00:34:55,830
... entrusted her kid to me...

471
00:34:57,955 --> 00:35:00,290
It's God's doing.

472
00:35:22,371 --> 00:35:24,415
If you make that decision...

473
00:35:26,331 --> 00:35:28,227
...then you're no longer my daughter.

474
00:35:28,331 --> 00:35:30,522
Honey, think about what you are saying.

475
00:35:32,455 --> 00:35:35,291
- So, you agree with this?
- I don't.

476
00:35:35,371 --> 00:35:40,291
I don't agree to our daughter marrying a married man.

477
00:35:40,371 --> 00:35:44,455
But Cathy will forever be our daughter.

478
00:35:46,955 --> 00:35:48,999
A daughter who disappoints us...

479
00:35:49,079 --> 00:35:52,455
...because she changed her belief
to chase Malik's love?

480
00:35:54,831 --> 00:35:59,246
Mom, I became a Muslim not because of Malik.

481
00:36:00,291 --> 00:36:05,123
I had broken up with him back then.

482
00:36:07,407 --> 00:36:09,999
So, it had nothing to do with him.

483
00:36:10,079 --> 00:36:12,915
Stop it. Don't say anything anymore.

484
00:36:12,999 --> 00:36:15,830
This matter is clear.
We don't need to continue talking about this.

485
00:36:19,079 --> 00:36:20,123
Mom...

486
00:36:21,791 --> 00:36:22,830
Dad...

487
00:36:25,747 --> 00:36:27,202
I'm sorry...

488
00:36:29,207 --> 00:36:30,371
...for...

489
00:36:31,871 --> 00:36:34,246
...always disappointing you.

490
00:36:36,375 --> 00:36:41,586
But I have a reason for doing this.

491
00:36:45,871 --> 00:36:49,038
Whatever your reason is, I don't get it!

492
00:36:55,163 --> 00:36:58,139
We put you in school to be a smart woman!

493
00:36:58,915 --> 00:37:00,247
And what's the result?

494
00:37:01,775 --> 00:37:03,954
You're going to become someone's second wife.

495
00:37:05,623 --> 00:37:07,746
What sect are you following?

496
00:37:30,695 --> 00:37:33,026
So, can we start, Sir?

497
00:37:43,247 --> 00:37:44,371
Yes.

498
00:37:45,871 --> 00:37:48,291
In the name of Allah.

499
00:37:48,371 --> 00:37:54,623
I marry off and I wed off
Malik Al Fateeh bin Muhammad Yahya...

500
00:37:54,707 --> 00:37:58,707
...with Cathalina Gilia binti Paul Wijaya...

501
00:37:58,791 --> 00:38:03,039
...with the dowry a set of prayer kits, in cash.

502
00:38:03,123 --> 00:38:07,122
I accept Cathalina Gilia binti Paul...

503
00:38:41,123 --> 00:38:42,414
Go on.

504
00:38:56,247 --> 00:38:58,998
What do you think? We go back from the start?

505
00:39:02,831 --> 00:39:05,455
In the name of Allah.

506
00:39:05,539 --> 00:39:12,707
I marry off and I wed off
Malik Al Fateeh bin Muhammad Yahya...

507
00:39:12,791 --> 00:39:16,539
...with Cathalina Gilia binti Paul Wijaya...

508
00:39:16,623 --> 00:39:20,831
...with the dowry a set of prayer kits, in cash.

